    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="660" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Whitehouse</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Whitehouse telegraphs that the restrictions against such hog products
                            as may he accompanied by health certificate have been removed by the
                            Government of Italy. He states that live pigs are not included, the
                            decree being still in force against their importation.</p>
            </div>
